    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Black Walnut is the warm anchor of the Landmark catalog. It reads as a clear deep brown in direct sun and softens into a near-black on overcast days. The granule blend leans warm, with reddish or amber accents that give the surface a sense of depth most gray shingles cannot match.",
      "The shingle profile carries a deep shadow line that emphasizes the warm tones in late-afternoon light. At dusk the entire roof becomes one quiet warm plane that ties the house into the landscape.",
      "Difficult to use poorly on a craftsman, traditional, or Tudor home. Harder to specify on a stark modern build where the warmth of the roof can fight the rest of the palette."
    ],
